.TH DOC-HUB 1 "2026-03-26" "doc-hub 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
doc-hub \- unified documentation search and pipeline CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B doc-hub
.RI [ command ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
doc-hub works with registered corpora, search, pipeline evaluation, and MCP serving.
Keep to the top-level command tree and use the examples below as a quick reference.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B doc-hub docs list
List registered corpora.
.TP
.B doc-hub man
Print the built-in manual page.
.TP
.B doc-hub docs search --corpus CORPUS [--corpus CORPUS ...] "QUERY"
Search one or more corpora.
.TP
.B doc-hub docs browse CORPUS
Browse persisted corpus documents and short IDs.
.TP
.B doc-hub docs read CORPUS DOC_PATH_OR_ID
Read a document by path or short document ID.
.TP
.B doc-hub pipeline add <name> --strategy {llms_txt,sitemap,git_repo,local_dir} [--url URL] [--path PATH] [--slug SLUG] [--no-index] [--url-pattern PATTERN] [--base-url URL] [--workers N] [--retries N] [--branch BRANCH] [--docs-dir DIR]
Register a new documentation corpus and run the full indexing pipeline.
The name is required (positional).
The \fB\-\-strategy\fR flag selects the fetcher plugin.
Strategy-specific flags: \fB\-\-url\fR (required for llms_txt, sitemap, git_repo),
\fB\-\-path\fR (required for local_dir).
A slug is auto-derived from the name unless \fB\-\-slug\fR is provided.
Use \fB\-\-no-index\fR to register without running the pipeline.
.TP
.B doc-hub pipeline run --corpus CORPUS
Run the pipeline against a corpus.
.TP
.B doc-hub pipeline logs <slug>
Run the indexing pipeline for an existing corpus with visible log output.
Useful for monitoring pipeline progress and diagnosing issues.
.TP
.B doc-hub serve mcp
Start the MCP server.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
List the available corpora:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub docs list
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show the bundled CLI reference text directly:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub man
.fi
.RE
.PP
Search one corpus:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub docs search --corpus pydantic-ai "retry logic"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Search multiple corpora:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub docs search --corpus pydantic-ai --corpus fastapi "retry middleware"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Browse and read documentation:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub docs browse pydantic-ai
doc-hub docs read pydantic-ai agents
doc-hub docs read pydantic-ai abc123
.fi
.RE
.PP
Register a new corpus and index it:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub pipeline add "Pydantic AI" --strategy llms_txt --url https://ai.pydantic.dev/llms.txt
.fi
.RE
.PP
Register a local directory corpus without indexing:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub pipeline add "My Docs" --strategy local_dir --path ./docs --no-index
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run the pipeline for one corpus:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub pipeline run --corpus pydantic-ai
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run the pipeline with visible logs:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub pipeline logs pydantic-ai
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start the MCP server:
.PP
.RS
.nf
doc-hub serve mcp
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DOC_HUB_DATA_DIR
Overrides the local data directory used for the database and env file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $DOC_HUB_DATA_DIR/env
Optional local environment overrides loaded by the CLI.
